name: 5. Entry to Another World
description:
"The gate that lead to our driveway, the shipping container we could never find a trucker adventurous enough to take down, the washing machine I had collected to turn into a wind turbine. These were familiar markers of a place I knew. But the sky was a haze, the lighting was off. We were on another planet, it seemed. It was like a movie set for a science fiction film, nothing felt real. Any minute someone would yell "Cut" and we would go to lunch, I wished. At least we didn't have to worry about closing the gate anymore.. not that it was still standing anyway."

Photography by Jay Moon, during the Australian wildfires; November 2019.
